210template <class T>
211class Local {
212 public:
213 V8_INLINE Local() : val_(0) {}
214 template <class S>
215 V8_INLINE Local(Local<S> that)
216 : val_(reinterpret_cast<T*>(*that)) {
222 TYPE_CHECK(T, S);
223 }
224
228 V8_INLINE bool IsEmpty() const { return val_ == 0; }
229
233 V8_INLINE void Clear() { val_ = 0; }
234
235 V8_INLINE T* operator->() const { return val_; }
236
237 V8_INLINE T* operator*() const { return val_; }
238
245 template <class S>
246 V8_INLINE bool operator==(const Local<S>& that) const {
247 internal::Object** a = reinterpret_cast<internal::Object**>(this->val_);
248 internal::Object** b = reinterpret_cast<internal::Object**>(that.val_);
249 if (a == 0) return b == 0;
250 if (b == 0) return false;
251 return *a == *b;
252 }
253
254 template <class S> V8_INLINE bool operator==(
255 const PersistentBase<S>& that) const {
256 internal::Object** a = reinterpret_cast<internal::Object**>(this->val_);
257 internal::Object** b = reinterpret_cast<internal::Object**>(that.val_);
258 if (a == 0) return b == 0;
259 if (b == 0) return false;
260 return *a == *b;
261 }
262
269 template <class S>
270 V8_INLINE bool operator!=(const Local<S>& that) const {
271 return !operator==(that);
272 }
273
274 template <class S> V8_INLINE bool operator!=(
275 const Persistent<S>& that) const {
276 return !operator==(that);
277 }
278
279 template <class S> V8_INLINE static Local<T> Cast(Local<S> that) {
280#ifdef V8_ENABLE_CHECKS
281 // If we're going to perform the type check then we have to check
282 // that the handle isn't empty before doing the checked cast.
283 if (that.IsEmpty()) return Local<T>();
284#endif
285 return Local<T>(T::Cast(*that));
286 }

288
289 template <class S> V8_INLINE Local<S> As() {
290 return Local<S>::Cast(*this);
291 }
292
298 V8_INLINE static Local<T> New(Isolate* isolate, Local<T> that);
299 V8_INLINE static Local<T> New(Isolate* isolate,
300 const PersistentBase<T>& that);
301
302 private:
303 friend class Utils;
304 template<class F> friend class Eternal;
305 template<class F> friend class PersistentBase;
306 template<class F, class M> friend class Persistent;
307 template<class F> friend class Local;
308 template <class F>
309 friend class MaybeLocal;
310 template<class F> friend class FunctionCallbackInfo;
311 template<class F> friend class PropertyCallbackInfo;
312 friend class String;
313 friend class Object;
314 friend class Context;
315 friend class Private;
316 template<class F> friend class internal::CustomArguments;
317 friend Local<Primitive> Undefined(Isolate* isolate);
318 friend Local<Primitive> Null(Isolate* isolate);
319 friend Local<Boolean> True(Isolate* isolate);
320 friend Local<Boolean> False(Isolate* isolate);

322 friend class EscapableHandleScope;

324 friend class PersistentValueMapBase;
325 template<class F1, class F2> friend class PersistentValueVector;

327 template <class S>
328 V8_INLINE Local(S* that)
329 : val_(that) {}
330 V8_INLINE static Local<T> New(Isolate* isolate, T* that);
331 T* val_;
332};

352template <class T>
353class MaybeLocal {
354 public:
355 V8_INLINE MaybeLocal() : val_(nullptr) {}
356 template <class S>
357 V8_INLINE MaybeLocal(Local<S> that)
358 : val_(reinterpret_cast<T*>(*that)) {
359 TYPE_CHECK(T, S);
360 }
361
362 V8_INLINE bool IsEmpty() const { return val_ == nullptr; }
363
364 template <class S>
365 V8_WARN_UNUSED_RESULT V8_INLINE bool ToLocal(Local<S>* out) const {
366 out->val_ = IsEmpty() ? nullptr : this->val_;
367 return !IsEmpty();
368 }
369
370 // Will crash if the MaybeLocal<> is empty.
371 V8_INLINE Local<T> ToLocalChecked();
372
373 template <class S>
374 V8_INLINE Local<S> FromMaybe(Local<S> default_value) const {
375 return IsEmpty() ? default_value : Local<S>(val_);
376 }
377
378 private:
379 T* val_;
380};

398 int index_;
399};

405template <typename T>
406class WeakCallbackInfo {
407 public:
408 typedef void (*Callback)(const WeakCallbackInfo<T>& data);
409
410 WeakCallbackInfo(Isolate* isolate, T* parameter,
411 void* internal_fields[kInternalFieldsInWeakCallback],
412 Callback* callback)
413 : isolate_(isolate), parameter_(parameter), callback_(callback) {
414 for (int i = 0; i < kInternalFieldsInWeakCallback; ++i) {
415 internal_fields_[i] = internal_fields[i];
416 }
417 }
418
419 V8_INLINE Isolate* GetIsolate() const { return isolate_; }
420 V8_INLINE T* GetParameter() const { return parameter_; }
421 V8_INLINE void* GetInternalField(int index) const;
422
423 V8_INLINE V8_DEPRECATE_SOON("use indexed version",
424 void* GetInternalField1() const) {
425 return internal_fields_[0];
426 }
427 V8_INLINE V8_DEPRECATE_SOON("use indexed version",
428 void* GetInternalField2() const) {
429 return internal_fields_[1];
430 }
431
432 bool IsFirstPass() const { return callback_ != nullptr; }
433
434 // When first called, the embedder MUST Reset() the Global which triggered the
435 // callback. The Global itself is unusable for anything else. No v8 other api
436 // calls may be called in the first callback. Should additional work be
437 // required, the embedder must set a second pass callback, which will be
438 // called after all the initial callbacks are processed.
439 // Calling SetSecondPassCallback on the second pass will immediately crash.
440 void SetSecondPassCallback(Callback callback) const { *callback_ = callback; }
441
442 private:
443 Isolate* isolate_;
444 T* parameter_;
445 Callback* callback_;
446 void* internal_fields_[kInternalFieldsInWeakCallback];
447};

553 template <typename P>
554 V8_INLINE V8_DEPRECATE_SOON(
555 "use WeakCallbackInfo version",
556 void SetWeak(P* parameter,
557 typename WeakCallbackData<T, P>::Callback callback));
558
559 template <typename S, typename P>
560 V8_INLINE V8_DEPRECATE_SOON(
561 "use WeakCallbackInfo version",
562 void SetWeak(P* parameter,
563 typename WeakCallbackData<S, P>::Callback callback));
564
565 // Phantom persistents work like weak persistents, except that the pointer to
566 // the object being collected is not available in the finalization callback.
567 // This enables the garbage collector to collect the object and any objects
568 // it references transitively in one GC cycle. At the moment you can either
569 // specify a parameter for the callback or the location of two internal
570 // fields in the dying object.
571 template <typename P>
572 V8_INLINE V8_DEPRECATE_SOON(
573 "use SetWeak",
574 void SetPhantom(P* parameter,
575 typename WeakCallbackInfo<P>::Callback callback,
576 int internal_field_index1 = -1,
577 int internal_field_index2 = -1));
578
579 template <typename P>
580 V8_INLINE void SetWeak(P* parameter,
581 typename WeakCallbackInfo<P>::Callback callback,
582 WeakCallbackType type);
583
584 template<typename P>
585 V8_INLINE P* ClearWeak();
586
587 // TODO(dcarney): remove this.
588 V8_INLINE void ClearWeak() { ClearWeak<void>(); }

596 V8_INLINE void MarkIndependent();

607
613 V8_INLINE void MarkActive();

615 V8_INLINE bool IsIndependent() const;

619
621 V8_INLINE bool IsWeak() const;
622
627 V8_INLINE void SetWrapperClassId(uint16_t class_id);
628
633 V8_INLINE uint16_t WrapperClassId() const;

635 private:
636 friend class Isolate;
637 friend class Utils;
638 template<class F> friend class Local;

647 friend class Object;

705template <class T, class M> class Persistent : public PersistentBase<T> {
706 public:
710 V8_INLINE Persistent() : PersistentBase<T>(0) { }
716 template <class S>
717 V8_INLINE Persistent(Isolate* isolate, Local<S> that)
718 : PersistentBase<T>(PersistentBase<T>::New(isolate, *that)) {
719 TYPE_CHECK(T, S);
720 }
726 template <class S, class M2>
727 V8_INLINE Persistent(Isolate* isolate, const Persistent<S, M2>& that)
728 : PersistentBase<T>(PersistentBase<T>::New(isolate, *that)) {
729 TYPE_CHECK(T, S);
730 }
737 V8_INLINE Persistent(const Persistent& that) : PersistentBase<T>(0) {
738 Copy(that);
739 }
740 template <class S, class M2>
741 V8_INLINE Persistent(const Persistent<S, M2>& that) : PersistentBase<T>(0) {
742 Copy(that);
743 }
744 V8_INLINE Persistent& operator=(const Persistent& that) { // NOLINT
745 Copy(that);
746 return *this;
747 }
748 template <class S, class M2>
749 V8_INLINE Persistent& operator=(const Persistent<S, M2>& that) { // NOLINT
750 Copy(that);
751 return *this;
752 }
758 V8_INLINE ~Persistent() {
759 if (M::kResetInDestructor) this->Reset();
760 }
761
762 // TODO(dcarney): this is pretty useless, fix or remove
763 template <class S>
764 V8_INLINE static Persistent<T>& Cast(Persistent<S>& that) { // NOLINT
765#ifdef V8_ENABLE_CHECKS
766 // If we're going to perform the type check then we have to check
767 // that the handle isn't empty before doing the checked cast.
768 if (!that.IsEmpty()) T::Cast(*that);
769#endif
770 return reinterpret_cast<Persistent<T>&>(that);
771 }
772
773 // TODO(dcarney): this is pretty useless, fix or remove
774 template <class S> V8_INLINE Persistent<S>& As() { // NOLINT
775 return Persistent<S>::Cast(*this);
776 }
777
778 private:
779 friend class Isolate;
780 friend class Utils;
781 template<class F> friend class Local;
782 template<class F1, class F2> friend class Persistent;
783 template<class F> friend class ReturnValue;
784
785 template <class S> V8_INLINE Persistent(S* that) : PersistentBase<T>(that) { }
786 V8_INLINE T* operator*() const { return this->val_; }
787 template<class S, class M2>
788 V8_INLINE void Copy(const Persistent<S, M2>& that);
789};

797template <class T>
798class Global : public PersistentBase<T> {
799 public:
803 V8_INLINE Global() : PersistentBase<T>(nullptr) {}
809 template <class S>
810 V8_INLINE Global(Isolate* isolate, Local<S> that)
811 : PersistentBase<T>(PersistentBase<T>::New(isolate, *that)) {

813 }
819 template <class S>
820 V8_INLINE Global(Isolate* isolate, const PersistentBase<S>& that)
821 : PersistentBase<T>(PersistentBase<T>::New(isolate, that.val_)) {
822 TYPE_CHECK(T, S);
823 }
827 V8_INLINE Global(Global&& other) : PersistentBase<T>(other.val_) { // NOLINT
828 other.val_ = nullptr;
829 }
830 V8_INLINE ~Global() { this->Reset(); }
834 template <class S>
835 V8_INLINE Global& operator=(Global<S>&& rhs) { // NOLINT
836 TYPE_CHECK(T, S);
837 if (this != &rhs) {
838 this->Reset();
839 this->val_ = rhs.val_;
840 rhs.val_ = nullptr;
841 }
842 return *this;
843 }
847 Global Pass() { return static_cast<Global&&>(*this); } // NOLINT
848
849 /*
850 * For compatibility with Chromium's base::Bind (base::Passed).
851 */
852 typedef void MoveOnlyTypeForCPP03;
853

855 template <class F>
856 friend class ReturnValue;
857 Global(const Global&) = delete;
858 void operator=(const Global&) = delete;
859 V8_INLINE T* operator*() const { return this->val_; }
860};

998class ScriptOriginOptions {
999 public:
1000 V8_INLINE ScriptOriginOptions(bool is_embedder_debug_script = false,
1001 bool is_shared_cross_origin = false,
1002 bool is_opaque = false)
1003 : flags_((is_embedder_debug_script ? kIsEmbedderDebugScript : 0) |

1006 V8_INLINE ScriptOriginOptions(int flags)
1007 : flags_(flags &
1008 (kIsEmbedderDebugScript | kIsSharedCrossOrigin | kIsOpaque)) {}
1009 bool IsEmbedderDebugScript() const {
1010 return (flags_ & kIsEmbedderDebugScript) != 0;
1011 }
1012 bool IsSharedCrossOrigin() const {
1013 return (flags_ & kIsSharedCrossOrigin) != 0;
1014 }
1015 bool IsOpaque() const { return (flags_ & kIsOpaque) != 0; }
1016 int Flags() const { return flags_; }
1017
1018 private:
1019 enum {
1020 kIsEmbedderDebugScript = 1,
1021 kIsSharedCrossOrigin = 1 << 1,
1022 kIsOpaque = 1 << 2
1023 };
1024 const int flags_;
1025};

1132class V8_EXPORT ScriptCompiler {
1133 public:
1141 struct V8_EXPORT CachedData {
1142 enum BufferPolicy {
1143 BufferNotOwned,
1144 BufferOwned
1145 };
1146
1147 CachedData()
1148 : data(NULL),
1149 length(0),
1150 rejected(false),
1151 buffer_policy(BufferNotOwned) {}
1152
1153 // If buffer_policy is BufferNotOwned, the caller keeps the ownership of
1154 // data and guarantees that it stays alive until the CachedData object is
1155 // destroyed. If the policy is BufferOwned, the given data will be deleted
1156 // (with delete[]) when the CachedData object is destroyed.
1157 CachedData(const uint8_t* data, int length,
1158 BufferPolicy buffer_policy = BufferNotOwned);
1159 ~CachedData();
1160 // TODO(marja): Async compilation; add constructors which take a callback
1161 // which will be called when V8 no longer needs the data.
1162 const uint8_t* data;
1163 int length;
1164 bool rejected;
1165 BufferPolicy buffer_policy;
1166
1167 private:
1168 // Prevent copying. Not implemented.
1169 CachedData(const CachedData&);
1170 CachedData& operator=(const CachedData&);
1171 };

5155struct JitCodeEvent {
5156 enum EventType {
5157 CODE_ADDED,
5158 CODE_MOVED,
5159 CODE_REMOVED,
5160 CODE_ADD_LINE_POS_INFO,
5161 CODE_START_LINE_INFO_RECORDING,
5162 CODE_END_LINE_INFO_RECORDING
5163 };
5164 // Definition of the code position type. The "POSITION" type means the place
5165 // in the source code which are of interest when making stack traces to
5166 // pin-point the source location of a stack frame as close as possible.
5167 // The "STATEMENT_POSITION" means the place at the beginning of each
5168 // statement, and is used to indicate possible break locations.
5169 enum PositionType { POSITION, STATEMENT_POSITION };
5170
5171 // Type of event.
5172 EventType type;
5173 // Start of the instructions.
5174 void* code_start;
5175 // Size of the instructions.
5176 size_t code_len;
5177 // Script info for CODE_ADDED event.
5178 Local<UnboundScript> script;
5179 // User-defined data for *_LINE_INFO_* event. It's used to hold the source
5180 // code line information which is returned from the
5181 // CODE_START_LINE_INFO_RECORDING event. And it's passed to subsequent
5182 // CODE_ADD_LINE_POS_INFO and CODE_END_LINE_INFO_RECORDING events.
5183 void* user_data;
5184
5185 struct name_t {
5186 // Name of the object associated with the code, note that the string is not
5187 // zero-terminated.
5188 const char* str;
5189 // Number of chars in str.
5190 size_t len;
5191 };
5192
5193 struct line_info_t {
5194 // PC offset
5195 size_t offset;
5196 // Code postion
5197 size_t pos;
5198 // The position type.
5199 PositionType position_type;
5200 };
5201
5202 union {
5203 // Only valid for CODE_ADDED.
5204 struct name_t name;
5205
5206 // Only valid for CODE_ADD_LINE_POS_INFO
5207 struct line_info_t line_info;
5208
5209 // New location of instructions. Only valid for CODE_MOVED.
5210 void* new_code_start;
5211 };
5212};

5218 kJitCodeEventDefault = 0,
5219 // Generate callbacks for already existent code.
5220 kJitCodeEventEnumExisting = 1
5221};

6436template <class T>
6437class Maybe {
6438 public:
6439 V8_INLINE bool IsNothing() const { return !has_value; }
6440 V8_INLINE bool IsJust() const { return has_value; }
6441
6442 // Will crash if the Maybe<> is nothing.
6443 V8_INLINE T FromJust() const {
6444 if (V8_UNLIKELY(!IsJust())) V8::FromJustIsNothing();
6445 return value;
6446 }
6447
6448 V8_INLINE T FromMaybe(const T& default_value) const {
6449 return has_value ? value : default_value;
6450 }
6451
6452 V8_INLINE bool operator==(const Maybe& other) const {
6453 return (IsJust() == other.IsJust()) &&
6454 (!IsJust() || FromJust() == other.FromJust());
6455 }
6456
6457 V8_INLINE bool operator!=(const Maybe& other) const {
6458 return !operator==(other);
6459 }
6460
6461 private:
6462 Maybe() : has_value(false) {}
6463 explicit Maybe(const T& t) : has_value(true), value(t) {}
6464
6465 bool has_value;
6466 T value;
6467
6468 template <class U>
6469 friend Maybe<U> Nothing();
6470 template <class U>
6471 friend Maybe<U> Just(const U& u);
6472};
6473
6474
6475template <class T>
6476inline Maybe<T> Nothing() {
6477 return Maybe<T>();
6478}
6479
6480
6481template <class T>
6482inline Maybe<T> Just(const T& t) {
6483 return Maybe<T>(t);
6484}

6974const int kApiPointerSize = sizeof(void*); // NOLINT
6975const int kApiIntSize = sizeof(int); // NOLINT
6976const int kApiInt64Size = sizeof(int64_t); // NOLINT
6977
6978// Tag information for HeapObject.
6979const int kHeapObjectTag = 1;
6980const int kHeapObjectTagSize = 2;
6981const intptr_t kHeapObjectTagMask = (1 << kHeapObjectTagSize) - 1;
6982
6983// Tag information for Smi.
6984const int kSmiTag = 0;
6985const int kSmiTagSize = 1;
6986const intptr_t kSmiTagMask = (1 << kSmiTagSize) - 1;
6987
6988template <size_t ptr_size> struct SmiTagging;
6989
6990template<int kSmiShiftSize>
6991V8_INLINE internal::Object* IntToSmi(int value) {
6992 int smi_shift_bits = kSmiTagSize + kSmiShiftSize;
6993 uintptr_t tagged_value =
6994 (static_cast<uintptr_t>(value) << smi_shift_bits) | kSmiTag;
6995 return reinterpret_cast<internal::Object*>(tagged_value);
6996}
6997
6998// Smi constants for 32-bit systems.
6999template <> struct SmiTagging<4> {
7000 enum { kSmiShiftSize = 0, kSmiValueSize = 31 };
7001 static int SmiShiftSize() { return kSmiShiftSize; }
7002 static int SmiValueSize() { return kSmiValueSize; }
7003 V8_INLINE static int SmiToInt(const internal::Object* value) {
7004 int shift_bits = kSmiTagSize + kSmiShiftSize;
7005 // Throw away top 32 bits and shift down (requires >> to be sign extending).
7006 return static_cast<int>(reinterpret_cast<intptr_t>(value)) >> shift_bits;
7007 }
7008 V8_INLINE static internal::Object* IntToSmi(int value) {
7009 return internal::IntToSmi<kSmiShiftSize>(value);
7010 }
7011 V8_INLINE static bool IsValidSmi(intptr_t value) {
7012 // To be representable as an tagged small integer, the two
7013 // most-significant bits of 'value' must be either 00 or 11 due to
7014 // sign-extension. To check this we add 01 to the two
7015 // most-significant bits, and check if the most-significant bit is 0
7016 //
7017 // CAUTION: The original code below:
7018 // bool result = ((value + 0x40000000) & 0x80000000) == 0;
7019 // may lead to incorrect results according to the C language spec, and
7020 // in fact doesn't work correctly with gcc4.1.1 in some cases: The
7021 // compiler may produce undefined results in case of signed integer
7022 // overflow. The computation must be done w/ unsigned ints.
7023 return static_cast<uintptr_t>(value + 0x40000000U) < 0x80000000U;
7024 }
7025};
7026
7027// Smi constants for 64-bit systems.
7028template <> struct SmiTagging<8> {
7029 enum { kSmiShiftSize = 31, kSmiValueSize = 32 };
7030 static int SmiShiftSize() { return kSmiShiftSize; }
7031 static int SmiValueSize() { return kSmiValueSize; }
7032 V8_INLINE static int SmiToInt(const internal::Object* value) {
7033 int shift_bits = kSmiTagSize + kSmiShiftSize;
7034 // Shift down and throw away top 32 bits.
7035 return static_cast<int>(reinterpret_cast<intptr_t>(value) >> shift_bits);
7036 }
7037 V8_INLINE static internal::Object* IntToSmi(int value) {
7038 return internal::IntToSmi<kSmiShiftSize>(value);
7039 }
7040 V8_INLINE static bool IsValidSmi(intptr_t value) {
7041 // To be representable as a long smi, the value must be a 32-bit integer.
7042 return (value == static_cast<int32_t>(value));
7043 }
7044};
7045
7046typedef SmiTagging<kApiPointerSize> PlatformSmiTagging;
7047const int kSmiShiftSize = PlatformSmiTagging::kSmiShiftSize;
7048const int kSmiValueSize = PlatformSmiTagging::kSmiValueSize;
7049V8_INLINE static bool SmiValuesAre31Bits() { return kSmiValueSize == 31; }
7050V8_INLINE static bool SmiValuesAre32Bits() { return kSmiValueSize == 32; }

7202 V8_INLINE static T ReadField(const internal::Object* ptr, int offset) {
7203 const uint8_t* addr =
7204 reinterpret_cast<const uint8_t*>(ptr) + offset - kHeapObjectTag;

7208 template <typename T>
7209 V8_INLINE static T ReadEmbedderData(const v8::Context* context, int index) {
7210 typedef internal::Object O;
7211 typedef internal::Internals I;
7212 O* ctx = *reinterpret_cast<O* const*>(context);
7213 int embedder_data_offset = I::kContextHeaderSize +
7214 (internal::kApiPointerSize * I::kContextEmbedderDataIndex);
7215 O* embedder_data = I::ReadField<O*>(ctx, embedder_data_offset);
7216 int value_offset =
7217 I::kFixedArrayHeaderSize + (internal::kApiPointerSize * index);
7218 return I::ReadField<T>(embedder_data, value_offset);
7219 }

7721
7722Local<Value> Object::GetInternalField(int index) {
7723#ifndef V8_ENABLE_CHECKS
7724 typedef internal::Object O;
7725 typedef internal::HeapObject HO;
7726 typedef internal::Internals I;
7727 O* obj = *reinterpret_cast<O**>(this);
7728 // Fast path: If the object is a plain JSObject, which is the common case, we
7729 // know where to find the internal fields and can return the value directly.
7730 if (I::GetInstanceType(obj) == I::kJSObjectType) {
7731 int offset = I::kJSObjectHeaderSize + (internal::kApiPointerSize * index);
7732 O* value = I::ReadField<O*>(obj, offset);
7733 O** result = HandleScope::CreateHandle(reinterpret_cast<HO*>(obj), value);
7734 return Local<Value>(reinterpret_cast<Value*>(result));
7735 }
7736#endif
7737 return SlowGetInternalField(index);
7738}
7739
7740
7741void* Object::GetAlignedPointerFromInternalField(int index) {
7742#ifndef V8_ENABLE_CHECKS
7743 typedef internal::Object O;
7744 typedef internal::Internals I;
7745 O* obj = *reinterpret_cast<O**>(this);
7746 // Fast path: If the object is a plain JSObject, which is the common case, we
7747 // know where to find the internal fields and can return the value directly.
7748 if (V8_LIKELY(I::GetInstanceType(obj) == I::kJSObjectType)) {
7749 int offset = I::kJSObjectHeaderSize + (internal::kApiPointerSize * index);
7750 return I::ReadField<void*>(obj, offset);
7751 }
7752#endif
7753 return SlowGetAlignedPointerFromInternalField(index);
7754}

7774String::ExternalStringResource* String::GetExternalStringResource() const {
7775 typedef internal::Object O;
7776 typedef internal::Internals I;
7777 O* obj = *reinterpret_cast<O* const*>(this);
7778 String::ExternalStringResource* result;
7779 if (I::IsExternalTwoByteString(I::GetInstanceType(obj))) {
7780 void* value = I::ReadField<void*>(obj, I::kStringResourceOffset);
7781 result = reinterpret_cast<String::ExternalStringResource*>(value);
7782 } else {
7783 result = NULL;
7784 }
7785#ifdef V8_ENABLE_CHECKS
7786 VerifyExternalStringResource(result);
7787#endif
7788 return result;
7789}

7791
7792String::ExternalStringResourceBase* String::GetExternalStringResourceBase(
7793 String::Encoding* encoding_out) const {
7794 typedef internal::Object O;
7795 typedef internal::Internals I;
7796 O* obj = *reinterpret_cast<O* const*>(this);
7797 int type = I::GetInstanceType(obj) & I::kFullStringRepresentationMask;
7798 *encoding_out = static_cast<Encoding>(type & I::kStringEncodingMask);
7799 ExternalStringResourceBase* resource = NULL;
7800 if (type == I::kExternalOneByteRepresentationTag ||
7801 type == I::kExternalTwoByteRepresentationTag) {
7802 void* value = I::ReadField<void*>(obj, I::kStringResourceOffset);
7803 resource = static_cast<ExternalStringResourceBase*>(value);
7804 }
7805#ifdef V8_ENABLE_CHECKS
7806 VerifyExternalStringResourceBase(resource, *encoding_out);
7807#endif
7808 return resource;
7809}

8281
8282int64_t Isolate::AdjustAmountOfExternalAllocatedMemory(
8283 int64_t change_in_bytes) {
8284 typedef internal::Internals I;
8285 int64_t* amount_of_external_allocated_memory =
8286 reinterpret_cast<int64_t*>(reinterpret_cast<uint8_t*>(this) +
8287 I::kAmountOfExternalAllocatedMemoryOffset);
8288 int64_t* amount_of_external_allocated_memory_at_last_global_gc =
8289 reinterpret_cast<int64_t*>(
8290 reinterpret_cast<uint8_t*>(this) +
8291 I::kAmountOfExternalAllocatedMemoryAtLastGlobalGCOffset);
8292 int64_t amount = *amount_of_external_allocated_memory + change_in_bytes;
8293 if (change_in_bytes > 0 &&
8294 amount - *amount_of_external_allocated_memory_at_last_global_gc >
8295 I::kExternalAllocationLimit) {
8296 ReportExternalAllocationLimitReached();
8297 }
8298 *amount_of_external_allocated_memory = amount;
8299 return *amount_of_external_allocated_memory;
8300}
